div1.p: IN THE DISTRICT COURT OF THE UNITED STATES, FOR THE WESTERN DISTRICT OF WASHINGTON, NORTHERN DIVISION.

THE SPERRY & HUTCHINSON COMPANY, Plaintiff vs. CITY OF EVERETT, WASHINGTON; ROLAND H. HARTLEY, Mayor of said City; PETER D. KRABY, Chief of Police of said City, and BENJAMIN W. SHERWOOD, City Attorney, Defendants

This cause came on for hearing this 3rd day of September 1915, upon the stipulation of the parties to said action, for a dismissal of the above entitled action, and it appearing to the Court that said parties have entered into a stipulation on file in this action that an order may be entered dismissing the above entitles action without costs to either party, and the Court being fully advised in the premises,

IT IS ORDERED that the above entitled action be, and the same hereby is dismissed without prejudice and without costs to either party, and that the bond filed by the complainant on the issuing of a temporary injunction herein, be cancelled and that the principla and surety on said bond be, and they hereby are released of all liability thereunder.
DONE in Open Court this 3rd day of September 1915
Copy of the within received and due service of same acknowledged this day of 191 Attorney for
In the United States District Court for the Western District of Washington Northern Division
THE SPERRY & HUTCHINSON COMPANY Plaintiff v. City of Everett, et al., Defendants
FILED IN THE U.S. District Court Western of Washington NORTHERN DIVISION Sep 3 - 1915 FRANK CROSBY, Clerk
ATTORNEYS FOR 1503-1506 HOGE BUILDING SEATTLE, WASH.
At the office which they consent that service of all subsequent paper, except writs and process, may be made upon them
